00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:42,670
which had been following me around for over ten years...

273
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:47,539
thanks to you, Father.

274
00:21:51,519 --> 00:21:54,119
Just like how that incident was my fault,

275
00:21:57,789 --> 00:22:00,420
this incident isn't your fault either, Father.

276
00:22:01,319 --> 00:22:02,329
No.

277
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:07,329
Even if those things were our fault,

278
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:13,039
we just have to stop committing those sins from now on.

279
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:19,579
So Jin will be all right.

280
00:22:22,410 --> 00:22:23,450
I'm sure...

281
00:22:25,119 --> 00:22:26,119
she will be.

282
00:22:36,359 --> 00:22:37,559
Are you okay?

283
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,730
I was beaten up too much...

284
00:22:43,230 --> 00:22:44,700
to seem okay, wasn't I?

285
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,240
So,

286
00:22:49,509 --> 00:22:51,309
why did you come here?

287
00:22:57,279 --> 00:22:58,519
I know.

288
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:01,450
It's not like we communicated telepathically.

289
00:23:03,319 --> 00:23:06,259
But that crazy buddy told me where you were.

290
00:23:10,130 --> 00:23:13,730
Can you still make jokes in this kind of situation?

291
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:17,369
Why did you come to me when I was by the sea?

292
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:20,940
That was because...

293
00:23:20,941 --> 00:23:22,210
It's the same thing.

294
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:26,740
You're here.

295
00:23:27,609 --> 00:23:28,849
That's why I came here.

296
00:23:30,609 --> 00:23:32,420
Even though there was no telepathy.

297
00:23:33,319 --> 00:23:34,319
Even though...

298
00:23:36,349 --> 00:23:38,019
you're not my DNA Lover.

299
00:23:54,940 --> 00:23:57,240
I thought looking at the world through DNA...

300
00:23:59,609 --> 00:24:01,680
would make life easier.

301
00:24:05,119 --> 00:24:07,818
Mine was filled with misfortunes and unhappiness,

302
00:24:07,819 --> 00:24:09,849
and I wasn't sure I could survive.

303
00:24:12,289 --> 00:24:13,519
I believed that...

304
00:24:14,829 --> 00:24:17,660
if all this was fate predestined by my DNA,

305
00:24:19,029 --> 00:24:21,000
then one day, thanks to that DNA,

306
00:24:23,599 --> 00:24:26,640
I'd become happy once again.

307
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:31,309
So I proved it with my DNA and those of the people around me,

308
00:24:31,910 --> 00:24:35,209
and I even tried to enclose future incidents...

309
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:37,750
within my prediction range.

310
00:24:40,549 --> 00:24:42,819
That's how I believed I'd be happy.

311
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:48,460
But...

312
00:24:50,990 --> 00:24:52,859
whenever I see you,

313
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:58,869
my world that was built on DNA keeps crumbling.

314
00:25:03,039 --> 00:25:06,539
You always fall outside my prediction range,

315
00:25:09,349 --> 00:25:11,880
but I keep wanting to believe what you say.

316
00:25:14,079 --> 00:25:16,150
- So Jin. - I know.

317
00:25:17,089 --> 00:25:19,118
You don't believe things like this.

318
00:25:19,119 --> 00:25:20,119
I do.

319
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:27,660
I wondered all the way here.

320
00:25:30,430 --> 00:25:33,470
I lied and pretended to be your DNA Lover.

321
00:25:35,940 --> 00:25:37,910
I kept hanging around you.

322
00:25:39,980 --> 00:25:41,980
Could that be what got you in danger?

323
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:44,710
I was full of regret.

324
00:25:47,619 --> 00:25:49,420
I'm truly sorry...

325
00:25:50,819 --> 00:25:52,319
I put you through all this.

326
00:25:54,390 --> 00:25:55,660
No.

327
00:25:56,089 --> 00:25:57,929
Yeon Woo. Actually, today I...

328
00:25:57,930 --> 00:26:01,029
So I'll put everything back in place.

329
00:26:02,869 --> 00:26:04,369
Let's get out of here alive.

330
00:26:08,539 --> 00:26:12,009
Did either of our DNA say we'd die young?

331
00:26:15,809 --> 00:26:16,809
Did it?

332
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:20,049
I think I read something.

333
00:26:22,589 --> 00:26:23,789
No.

334
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:12,900
Hello, Mother. It's Mi Eun.

335
00:27:13,869 --> 00:27:15,910
I greeted you once last time.

336
00:27:16,769 --> 00:27:17,970
Do you remember?

337
00:27:19,009 --> 00:27:21,339
I didn't come to see Yeon Woo today.

338
00:27:22,549 --> 00:27:25,849
I heard you'd go to the US, so I came to say goodbye.

339
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:32,460
Promise me you'll get better there.

340
00:27:36,630 --> 00:27:39,660
You'll miss Korean food.

341
00:27:39,829 --> 00:27:43,230
I'll give Yeon Woo a list of good Korean restaurants.

342
00:27:49,609 --> 00:27:51,778
Forget all the bad things that happened...

343
00:27:51,779 --> 00:27:54,380
and live there happily with Yeon Woo.

344
00:28:14,329 --> 00:28:15,329
Nurse!

345
00:28:16,430 --> 00:28:17,430
Nurse!

346
00:28:27,710 --> 00:28:30,180
Ms. Yeom. Do you hear me?

347
00:28:30,950 --> 00:28:32,778
Do you know where you are?

348
00:28:32,779 --> 00:28:33,980
Pick up.

349
00:28:34,549 --> 00:28:36,619
The person you have reached is unavailable.

350
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,099
Yeon Woo, your mother's awake.

351
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:55,410
Call as soon as you get this. Your mother's waiting for you.

352
00:29:02,509 --> 00:29:04,009
That's enough. Let her go.

353
00:29:04,849 --> 00:29:06,579
She has nothing to do with me.

354
00:29:07,119 --> 00:29:08,619
I'm the one you want to kill.

355
00:29:11,990 --> 00:29:14,259
Both father and son are habitual liars.

356
00:29:17,390 --> 00:29:20,859
What do you think? It's not bad, is it?

357
00:29:24,869 --> 00:29:26,899
Father. I need to go to the restroom.

358
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:28,400
- Okay. - I won't be long.

359
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:45,089
Hello. I'm Yi Myung.

360
00:29:46,559 --> 00:29:48,630
You remember, don't you? Shin Yi Myung.

361
00:29:57,769 --> 00:30:01,269
Who could that be? I have no memory.

362
00:30:03,869 --> 00:30:06,740
You don't remember me?

363
00:30:07,380 --> 00:30:10,250
I don't know who you are, but could you excuse us?

364
00:30:10,779 --> 00:30:12,579
I'm with my family.

365
00:30:28,259 --> 00:30:29,269
Who was that?

366
00:30:29,430 --> 00:30:30,970
A complete stranger.

367
00:30:31,599 --> 00:30:34,200
I knew he wouldn't accept me as family,

368
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:38,240
but I was shocked to be called a stranger.

369
00:30:40,410 --> 00:30:42,048
Don't you think...

370
00:30:42,049 --> 00:30:44,450
your dad's way more of a jerk than me?

371
00:31:00,599 --> 00:31:01,859
One last question.

372
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:05,029
I have a lot to tell you, but so little time.

373
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:09,269
You needed a family, didn't you?

374
00:31:18,109 --> 00:31:20,579
I asked a question. Now answer.

375
00:31:22,250 --> 00:31:24,049
No. I'm done answering.

376
00:31:24,150 --> 00:31:25,920
You wasted the last question.

377
00:31:26,789 --> 00:31:27,819
That's a lie.

378
00:31:29,460 --> 00:31:30,460
What?

379
00:31:30,460 --> 00:31:31,460
Right.

380
00:31:32,329 --> 00:31:35,499
Are you a good liar because you're also his son?

381
00:31:35,500 --> 00:31:36,500
But you know,

382
00:31:37,529 --> 00:31:39,339
lying isn't hereditary.

383
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:43,409
What trick is this?

384
00:31:43,410 --> 00:31:44,910
You want to be happy.

385
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:48,539
You needed a family to love you.

386
00:31:49,410 --> 00:31:52,318
I felt the same my whole life,

387
00:31:52,319 --> 00:31:53,880
so I know the feeling.

388
00:31:56,190 --> 00:31:57,250
See?

389
00:31:57,819 --> 00:31:59,288
How can I let her go?

390
00:31:59,289 --> 00:32:00,559
So Jin.

391
00:32:00,759 --> 00:32:02,289
But you have a family.

392
00:32:03,829 --> 00:32:05,599
Your twin brother.

393
00:32:06,130 --> 00:32:08,160
Why do you think he became a priest?

394
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,869
You don't seem happy to see me at all.

395
00:32:15,809 --> 00:32:17,869
I've been hearing your voice.

396
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:20,240
What sin are you going to commit now?

397
00:32:20,339 --> 00:32:23,309
That's not a hallucination. You and I are one.

398
00:32:24,779 --> 00:32:26,919
I know what it is you're thinking.

399
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:30,019
Do you think confessing your sins will save you?

400
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,689
I saw Mom's soul get saved...

401
00:32:34,690 --> 00:32:36,559
as her body burned.

402
00:32:37,690 --> 00:32:39,759
I'll cleanse everything my way.

403
00:32:40,559 --> 00:32:43,170
I'll save people.

404
00:32:43,230 --> 00:32:45,099
Do you think that will save you?

405
00:32:45,839 --> 00:32:47,598
Atonement is the only way.

406
00:32:47,599 --> 00:32:49,109
Please stop what you're doing.

407
00:32:50,170 --> 00:32:51,170
Please.

408
00:32:51,339 --> 00:32:53,709
While you set fires and kill people...

409
00:32:53,710 --> 00:32:55,980
and justify it with your scars,

410
00:32:56,910 --> 00:33:01,019
Father Andrea spent his whole life praying for the wound to heal.

411
00:33:01,849 --> 00:33:04,818
You're twins who share the same DNA.

412
00:33:04,819 --> 00:33:07,960
Don't you think you're too different?

413
00:33:08,259 --> 00:33:09,460
Stop it, So Jin.

414
00:33:10,559 --> 00:33:12,929
Hey. Talk to me instead.

415
00:33:12,930 --> 00:33:14,460
She has nothing to do with it!

416
00:33:27,079 --> 00:33:28,240
The accident.

417
00:33:30,349 --> 00:33:31,750
It wasn't your fault.

418
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:36,190
It was just an accident.

419
00:33:37,619 --> 00:33:39,259
It was an accident,

420
00:33:40,789 --> 00:33:44,329
and you're blaming yourself for your mother's death.

421
00:33:49,329 --> 00:33:50,329
So what?

422
00:33:52,269 --> 00:33:54,869
You want me to return to my family and live happily?

423
00:33:57,170 --> 00:33:58,170
Yes.

424
00:33:59,210 --> 00:34:00,309
Stop right here.

425
00:34:01,710 --> 00:34:03,180
You can turn it back.

426
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:42,519
It's too late.

427
00:34:50,190 --> 00:34:54,159
Four, three, two, one.

428
00:34:56,969 --> 00:35:00,768
No! Help!

429
00:35:00,769 --> 00:35:02,939
- So Jin. - Hurry!

430
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:03,969
So Jin!

431
00:35:14,780 --> 00:35:17,190
So Jin, get yourself together. Are you okay?

432
00:35:17,619 --> 00:35:18,619
Get it together.

433
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:27,198
- Oh, gosh. - Get up.

434
00:35:27,199 --> 00:35:28,500
Let's go, So Jin.

435
00:35:33,940 --> 00:35:35,670
Be careful. Keep walking.

436
00:35:42,809 --> 00:35:45,348
- Yeon Woo... - So Jin. Go ahead.

437
00:35:45,349 --> 00:35:46,380
You go first.

438
00:36:24,650 --> 00:36:26,460
So Jin! Yeon Woo!

439
00:36:27,889 --> 00:36:28,889
Kang Hoon.

440
00:36:51,179 --> 00:36:52,179
Yi Myung.

441
00:36:56,619 --> 00:36:57,619
Yi Myung.

442
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:06,598
- Yi Myung! - No!

443
00:37:06,599 --> 00:37:08,229
- Yi Myung! - Stay here.

444
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:09,230
Yi Myung!

445
00:37:17,369 --> 00:37:18,809
You must die to end this.

446
00:37:30,289 --> 00:37:31,949
- Get out of here! - So Jin.

447
00:37:32,050 --> 00:37:33,289
So Jin.

448
00:37:37,260 --> 00:37:38,329
Careful.

449
00:37:40,630 --> 00:37:41,630
So Jin.

450
00:37:42,429 --> 00:37:44,500
So Jin! Are you okay?

451
00:37:44,869 --> 00:37:46,569
- Are you all right? - So Jin.

452
00:37:46,570 --> 00:37:47,768
- A Ri. - Yes?

453
00:37:47,769 --> 00:37:50,038
Keep talking to her so she doesn't pass out, okay?

454
00:37:50,039 --> 00:37:51,170
Okay.

455
00:37:51,269 --> 00:37:52,738
Wake up, So Jin.

456
00:37:52,739 --> 00:37:53,940
Stop him!

457
00:37:54,039 --> 00:37:55,809
- Stop him. - Seo Kang Hoon!

458
00:38:27,809 --> 00:38:29,210
I missed you, Mom.

459
00:38:36,550 --> 00:38:37,750
Let's get out of here.

460
00:38:38,289 --> 00:38:39,559
Live and pay for your crimes.

461
00:38:42,789 --> 00:38:43,789
Let's go.

462
00:39:03,949 --> 00:39:05,050
Shin Yi Myung.

463
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:09,889
Shin Yi Myung!

464
00:39:18,130 --> 00:39:19,130
Stop them.

465
00:39:24,099 --> 00:39:25,630
- Over here! - Okay.

466
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:29,538
- Excuse us. - Let us help.

467
00:39:29,539 --> 00:39:30,669
- Wake up! - Hang on.

468
00:39:30,670 --> 00:39:31,709
Let's take her.

469
00:39:31,710 --> 00:39:34,239
- One, two, three. - Let's move her.

470
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:37,679
- Let's lift her. One, two, three. - One, two, three.

471
00:39:45,590 --> 00:39:46,960
Where's my brother?

472
00:39:48,989 --> 00:39:50,889
Let's move in!

473
00:39:54,059 --> 00:39:55,229
Stay here.

474
00:39:55,230 --> 00:39:57,669
- Hey, get him. - My brother's in there.

475
00:39:57,670 --> 00:39:58,828
- Yi Myung! - You can't go inside.

476
00:39:58,829 --> 00:40:00,198
- Yi Myung! - You can't go.

477
00:40:00,199 --> 00:40:01,739
- Yi Myung! - Grab him.

478
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:02,939
Yi Myung!

479
00:40:02,940 --> 00:40:05,069
I said my brother's in there!

480
00:40:05,070 --> 00:40:06,308
- Yi Myung! - Please don't do this.

481
00:40:06,309 --> 00:40:07,609
- Are you okay? - Yi Myung!

482
00:40:07,610 --> 00:40:09,649
Are you all right? Were you hurt?

483
00:40:09,650 --> 00:40:11,480
- So Jin... - Yeon Woo!

484
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:14,078
- Take his legs. - Okay.

485
00:40:14,079 --> 00:40:15,789
- Let's go. - One, two, three.

486
00:40:16,090 --> 00:40:18,519
Excuse us! Coming through.

487
00:40:21,889 --> 00:40:23,389
- Hey! - Move!

488
00:40:29,969 --> 00:40:32,468
In Yeoncheon today, a man in his 30s...

489
00:40:32,469 --> 00:40:34,800
set fire to a vinyl greenhouse...

490
00:40:35,039 --> 00:40:37,739
before taking his own life.

491
00:40:38,039 --> 00:40:40,678
