545
00:44:00,210 --> 00:44:02,809
I heard you got stabbed.

546
00:44:03,380 --> 00:44:05,650
I wasn't stabbed.

547
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:08,050
I'm all healed and well. Look.

548
00:44:08,780 --> 00:44:11,019
Where were you hurt? How bad is it?

549
00:44:13,019 --> 00:44:15,759
See? It was a bad cut, wasn't it?

550
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:18,289
It's not like that.

551
00:44:19,059 --> 00:44:22,130
Don't mind me and focus on getting well.

552
00:44:58,769 --> 00:45:01,440
Why did you come to me when I was by the sea?

553
00:45:02,909 --> 00:45:04,110
It's the same thing.

554
00:45:07,079 --> 00:45:08,639
You're here.

555
00:45:09,650 --> 00:45:10,780
That's why I came here.

556
00:45:12,679 --> 00:45:14,480
Even though there was no telepathy.

557
00:45:15,380 --> 00:45:16,389
Even though...

558
00:45:18,349 --> 00:45:19,889
you're not my DNA Lover.

559
00:45:30,500 --> 00:45:31,699
Hello.

560
00:45:33,300 --> 00:45:34,440
Oh, Yeon Woo?

561
00:45:37,039 --> 00:45:39,369
(Registration and Payment)

562
00:45:49,820 --> 00:45:51,250
(Room 506, Sim)

563
00:46:12,539 --> 00:46:13,539
Yeon Woo.

564
00:46:14,809 --> 00:46:16,510
Wake up, will you?

565
00:46:19,650 --> 00:46:20,650
I still have...

566
00:46:22,449 --> 00:46:25,190
a lot to tell you.

567
00:46:56,650 --> 00:46:57,650
Hey.

568
00:46:59,590 --> 00:47:00,590
Hey.

569
00:47:05,730 --> 00:47:06,730
Hey.

570
00:47:07,730 --> 00:47:08,730
Yeon Woo.

571
00:47:10,599 --> 00:47:12,670
Are you all right? Are you awake?

572
00:47:13,039 --> 00:47:14,069
How's So Jin?

573
00:47:14,070 --> 00:47:15,440
She's fine.

574
00:47:15,570 --> 00:47:17,909
Wait right here. I'll get the doctor.

575
00:47:30,150 --> 00:47:31,249
My clothes are down there.

576
00:47:31,250 --> 00:47:32,448
You're not done yet?

577
00:47:32,449 --> 00:47:33,619
I'm almost done.

578
00:47:33,960 --> 00:47:34,960
Come in.

579
00:47:44,300 --> 00:47:46,369
Mom.

580
00:47:46,570 --> 00:47:48,099
So Ri called.

581
00:47:48,699 --> 00:47:50,909
I had an event in the area.

582
00:47:51,610 --> 00:47:52,979
So I dropped by.

583
00:47:52,980 --> 00:47:54,380
Does she have to talk like that?

584
00:47:55,710 --> 00:47:58,110
Don't mind me. Finish what you were doing.

585
00:48:01,280 --> 00:48:03,250
Yes. Please sit here.

586
00:48:05,550 --> 00:48:07,819
We have drinks in the refrigerator. Do you want something...

587
00:48:07,820 --> 00:48:09,489
No, I'm okay.

588
00:48:10,360 --> 00:48:12,729
Kang Hoon told me...

589
00:48:12,730 --> 00:48:16,428
that So Jin was almost killed several times by the kidnappers.

590
00:48:16,429 --> 00:48:19,530
Incidents like this can become a trauma.

591
00:48:19,940 --> 00:48:21,199
I'm worried.

592
00:48:28,480 --> 00:48:30,750
I'm fine.

593
00:48:31,010 --> 00:48:32,948
If things are tough, you can stay at my place.

594
00:48:32,949 --> 00:48:34,150
For a month or two.

595
00:48:40,719 --> 00:48:44,159
Well... I have to go overseas for work.

596
00:48:44,329 --> 00:48:46,900
I need someone to take care of the puppies.

597
00:49:00,510 --> 00:49:02,738
I'll be right back.

598
00:49:02,739 --> 00:49:05,209
Why? I took care of the discharge procedures.

599
00:49:05,210 --> 00:49:07,480
It's not that. Well...

600
00:49:07,750 --> 00:49:09,579
I want to say goodbye.

601
00:49:09,719 --> 00:49:12,090
Hold on. I'll be right back.

602
00:49:18,760 --> 00:49:20,360
Kidnapped? Can you believe it?

603
00:49:20,929 --> 00:49:22,559
What were the police doing?

604
00:49:22,900 --> 00:49:23,900
Goodness.

605
00:49:24,630 --> 00:49:25,699
How could...

606
00:49:26,739 --> 00:49:27,739
Pardon?

607
00:49:27,900 --> 00:49:29,268
What did you say?

608
00:49:29,269 --> 00:49:30,969
Well...

609
00:49:31,409 --> 00:49:34,539
I'll get going now.

610
00:49:37,610 --> 00:49:39,949
Tell So Jin to eat something nutritious.

611
00:49:40,579 --> 00:49:42,849
She looks awful.

612
00:49:52,429 --> 00:49:53,658
- So Jin. - Hey.

613
00:49:53,659 --> 00:49:55,428
I was on my way to see you.

614
00:49:55,429 --> 00:49:57,969
Yeon Woo just woke up.

615
00:49:58,570 --> 00:49:59,570
What?

616
00:50:08,239 --> 00:50:09,239
Yeon Woo.

617
00:50:10,449 --> 00:50:11,449
So Jin.

618
00:50:13,880 --> 00:50:15,149
Are you okay?

619
00:50:15,150 --> 00:50:17,288
What did the doctors say? Your arm...

620
00:50:17,289 --> 00:50:18,650
I think it's okay.

621
00:50:19,760 --> 00:50:20,989
How about you?

622
00:50:22,659 --> 00:50:24,429
I was so scared...

623
00:50:25,130 --> 00:50:26,760
that you wouldn't make it.

624
00:50:38,239 --> 00:50:41,110
I'm sorry that you got hurt because of me.

625
00:50:41,909 --> 00:50:43,809
You don't need to be sorry.

626
00:50:44,250 --> 00:50:46,250
It all happened because of me.

627
00:50:46,920 --> 00:50:47,920
Thank you...

628
00:50:48,949 --> 00:50:50,449
for hanging on in there.

629
00:50:51,090 --> 00:50:52,090
And...

630
00:50:53,159 --> 00:50:54,420
for being alive.

631
00:51:03,099 --> 00:51:06,328
What did they say about your arm?

632
00:51:06,329 --> 00:51:08,599
Is it really okay?

633
00:51:09,139 --> 00:51:11,969
It'll get better soon with reconstructive treatment.

634
00:51:12,409 --> 00:51:13,679
Don't worry.

635
00:51:18,050 --> 00:51:21,079
Once you recover, what happens after that?

636
00:51:26,789 --> 00:51:28,420
Do you still plan...

637
00:51:29,659 --> 00:51:31,130
to go to the US?

638
00:51:37,469 --> 00:51:38,599
If you're...

639
00:51:39,369 --> 00:51:41,300
leaving because of me,

640
00:51:42,400 --> 00:51:44,940
I wanted to tell you not to.

641
00:51:48,340 --> 00:51:52,179
I always thought I was the only one who got hurt in relationships,

642
00:51:53,550 --> 00:51:55,679
but I thought I was the one...

643
00:51:56,619 --> 00:51:58,690
who hurt you in this relationship.

644
00:52:00,019 --> 00:52:03,189
I was the one who suddenly entered your life,

645
00:52:03,190 --> 00:52:05,630
and I was the one who asked to do the experiment.

646
00:52:06,659 --> 00:52:08,199
So I no longer want...

647
00:52:08,559 --> 00:52:11,070
things to be uncomfortable for you because of me.

648
00:52:15,900 --> 00:52:17,070
I wasn't going to the US...

649
00:52:19,880 --> 00:52:21,610
just because of you.

650
00:52:23,809 --> 00:52:26,880
I said I'd put everything back in place.

651
00:52:27,420 --> 00:52:28,849
And my mother...

652
00:52:29,650 --> 00:52:31,190
and I...

653
00:52:31,989 --> 00:52:33,460
want to start fresh...

654
00:52:35,019 --> 00:52:36,559
in a new place.

655
00:52:40,329 --> 00:52:41,360
Who knows?

656
00:52:42,960 --> 00:52:45,869
Maybe I'll meet my real DNA lover there.

657
00:52:53,110 --> 00:52:54,880
Yeon Woo. I...

658
00:52:59,949 --> 00:53:01,079
You came.

659
00:53:01,150 --> 00:53:03,690
"You came?" Don't you know you almost died?

660
00:53:04,090 --> 00:53:06,448
What in the world happened? Are you okay?

661
00:53:06,449 --> 00:53:08,090
As you can see, I'm fine.

662
00:53:10,090 --> 00:53:13,760
I can't believe it. How could something like this happen?

663
00:53:15,460 --> 00:53:16,460
Hey.

664
00:53:16,900 --> 00:53:19,469
Who did this?

665
00:53:19,699 --> 00:53:21,239
Should I teach them a lesson?

666
00:53:21,599 --> 00:53:23,340
I'm in good form lately.

667
00:53:34,380 --> 00:53:38,420
Where Yi Myung used to be was a book.

668
00:53:39,960 --> 00:53:43,558
My Bible I didn't even notice he took.

669
00:53:43,559 --> 00:53:46,389
(The Holy Bible)

670
00:53:46,530 --> 00:53:48,860
In the place where everything burned,

671
00:53:49,400 --> 00:53:52,369
only this book survived unscathed.

672
00:53:54,239 --> 00:53:55,699
Could it be...

673
00:53:55,940 --> 00:53:58,739
because he desperately wanted to return it to me?

674
00:54:04,949 --> 00:54:08,280
In your Bible, the word, "Father," is mentioned hundreds of times.

675
00:54:09,750 --> 00:54:11,989
I had three fathers in my life.

676
00:54:12,920 --> 00:54:15,289
Although they all left me in the end.

677
00:54:17,559 --> 00:54:19,889
But my second father was a bit different.

678
00:54:20,929 --> 00:54:22,730
He gave me a dream...

679
00:54:23,099 --> 00:54:25,130
and cheered for my dream.

680
00:54:26,840 --> 00:54:28,369
It was a short time,

681
00:54:29,469 --> 00:54:33,309
but he was the one person I happily called father.

682
00:54:35,110 --> 00:54:38,510
I wanted to ask him one last time.

683
00:54:39,849 --> 00:54:42,119
Whether he really didn't remember me.

684
00:54:43,150 --> 00:54:44,619
Whether I was really...

685
00:54:45,750 --> 00:54:47,590
nothing to him.

686
00:54:48,559 --> 00:54:49,789
Who...

687
00:55:04,940 --> 00:55:06,238
How did you come here?

688
00:55:06,239 --> 00:55:08,579
You told me to call you father.

689
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:12,409
Why didn't you say you had...

690
00:55:13,420 --> 00:55:14,579
a wife and a son?

691
00:55:19,920 --> 00:55:22,219
We're not even connected by blood. How am I your father?

692
00:55:25,289 --> 00:55:27,158
What does something that happened 20 years ago...

693
00:55:27,159 --> 00:55:28,460
have anything to do with me?

694
00:55:31,199 --> 00:55:34,698
Did you know that Mother passed away?

695
00:55:34,699 --> 00:55:35,800
I know.

696
00:55:36,440 --> 00:55:38,009
I sponsored the orphanage...

697
00:55:38,010 --> 00:55:41,739
so you and your brother could eat and grow up well.

698
00:55:43,780 --> 00:55:46,250
I thought I made up for everything with that.

699
00:55:48,280 --> 00:55:50,150
What more can I do?

700
00:55:51,789 --> 00:55:52,789
Right.

701
00:55:53,320 --> 00:55:54,619
Do you need money?

702
00:55:57,929 --> 00:55:59,590
If you were going to forget that easily,

703
00:56:00,860 --> 00:56:02,799
why did you start something so meaningless?

704
00:56:02,800 --> 00:56:04,729
If you don't leave right away, I'll call the police.

705
00:56:04,730 --> 00:56:06,800
I never had a son like you.

706
00:56:06,869 --> 00:56:09,969
So don't ever come to me again. Do you understand?

707
00:56:12,210 --> 00:56:13,440
Get out.

708
00:56:19,380 --> 00:56:21,449
I'll never come back again.

709
00:56:23,849 --> 00:56:25,250
Goodbye, sir.

710
00:56:36,329 --> 00:56:38,529
(I wanted to ask. Whether he really didn't remember me.)

711
00:56:38,530 --> 00:56:41,070
(Whether I was really nothing to him.)

712
00:56:57,289 --> 00:56:58,289
Come in.

713
00:57:01,519 --> 00:57:03,489
- Hello. - Hello, Doctor.

714
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:06,630
How are you feeling? You must feel some pain.

715
00:57:07,329 --> 00:57:09,099
It's bearable.

716
00:57:09,230 --> 00:57:10,530
How am I looking?

717
00:57:11,530 --> 00:57:14,138
The emergency treatment went well.

718
00:57:14,139 --> 00:57:16,469
To tell you about your current condition,

719
00:57:17,010 --> 00:57:18,908
you got a burn on your palm, and the muscle and ligament...

720
00:57:18,909 --> 00:57:22,238
connecting your elbow to your fingers were damaged.

721
00:57:22,239 --> 00:57:25,150
That means you might see stiffening of the finger muscles.

722
00:57:27,280 --> 00:57:28,448
Stiffening?

723
00:57:28,449 --> 00:57:30,190
To explain it in simple terms,

724
00:57:30,590 --> 00:57:34,389
you might not be able to move the damaged area.

725
00:57:34,860 --> 00:57:36,959
Of course, in the worst-case scenario.

726
00:57:36,960 --> 00:57:38,760
Not be able to move?

727
00:57:39,289 --> 00:57:40,959
When will I start to see symptoms?

728
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:43,029
The stiffening might not happen right away,

729
00:57:43,030 --> 00:57:44,869
but it could gradually get worse.

730
00:57:45,500 --> 00:57:48,639
You should get specialized care at Sim General Hospital.

731
00:57:48,869 --> 00:57:50,809
They'll need to monitor your condition.

732
00:58:01,750 --> 00:58:02,880
Yeon Woo.

733
00:58:03,619 --> 00:58:05,750
You shouldn't stand up like that yet, Mom.

734
00:58:06,920 --> 00:58:07,920
Did you...

735
00:58:08,960 --> 00:58:10,229
Did you get hurt?

736
00:58:10,230 --> 00:58:11,530
It's nothing.

737
00:58:12,889 --> 00:58:13,900
Please sit.

738
00:58:22,769 --> 00:58:24,110
I didn't know,

739
00:58:24,769 --> 00:58:28,639
but I guess people suspected that I killed your dad.

740
00:58:30,309 --> 00:58:32,280
I was told that the culprit was caught.

741
00:58:32,880 --> 00:58:34,579
They want to hear what happened that day.

742
00:58:36,719 --> 00:58:38,690
When you were unconscious,

743
00:58:40,590 --> 00:58:42,889
you were always smiling. You didn't know that, did you?

744
00:58:47,260 --> 00:58:50,530
I saw your dad in my dream.

745
00:58:52,530 --> 00:58:54,840
Was it because of the sound of that music box?

746
00:58:57,809 --> 00:58:59,769
It's the piece I played...

747
00:59:00,579 --> 00:59:02,409
on the first day I met your dad.

748
00:59:04,710 --> 00:59:08,018
He was just as young and handsome...

749
00:59:08,019 --> 00:59:09,420
as he was the first day we met.

750
00:59:10,289 --> 00:59:13,819
Your father said he fell for me when he came...

751
00:59:13,820 --> 00:59:16,119
to my first solo recital.

752
00:59:19,760 --> 00:59:21,599
He kept saying that in my dream.

753
00:59:22,059 --> 00:59:23,829
Mi Eun gave you a nice gift.

754
00:59:24,699 --> 00:59:25,769
Mi Eun?

755
00:59:26,130 --> 00:59:28,000
Oh, your friend?

756
00:59:28,670 --> 00:59:31,638
She was pretty. She's the girl you like, isn't she?

757
00:59:31,639 --> 00:59:32,639
She's a friend.

758
00:59:34,639 --> 00:59:35,639
Yeon Woo.

759
00:59:36,239 --> 00:59:37,510
I resented...

760
00:59:38,409 --> 00:59:40,179
your father so much.

761
00:59:42,150 --> 00:59:43,179
But all I thought...

762
00:59:45,849 --> 00:59:48,260
in that moment was that I should save him.

763
00:59:55,360 --> 00:59:56,599
Honey!

764
00:59:57,030 --> 00:59:58,030
Honey!

765
00:59:58,869 --> 00:59:59,869
Don't come.

766
00:59:59,870 --> 01:00:02,138
Honey!

767
01:00:02,139 --> 01:00:03,139
Honey.

768
01:00:16,019 --> 01:00:17,719
That's how our last moments went.

769
01:00:18,119 --> 01:00:19,920
Because we wanted to save each other,

770
01:00:23,889 --> 01:00:25,889
we weren't afraid of dying at all.

771
01:00:31,500 --> 01:00:33,999
Yeon Woo. Your hand!

772
01:00:34,000 --> 01:00:35,239
- Your hand. - So Jin. Go first.

773
01:00:35,570 --> 01:00:36,800
After that,

774
01:00:37,170 --> 01:00:40,440
I got the courage to live my life.

775
01:00:43,440 --> 01:00:47,050
The thing that was tying me down my whole life...

776
01:00:48,650 --> 01:00:50,150
wasn't love.

777
01:00:52,449 --> 01:00:54,019
It was resentment.

778
01:01:03,800 --> 01:01:05,699
I'm almost all better, right?

779
01:01:07,800 --> 01:01:10,469
What happened to your arm?

780
01:01:11,010 --> 01:01:12,209
It's really nothing.

781
01:01:12,210 --> 01:01:14,280
It looks like something.

782
01:01:14,510 --> 01:01:15,510
This...

783
01:01:22,349 --> 01:01:23,519
I'm sorry.

784
01:01:31,130 --> 01:01:33,130
I wasn't a good mom.

785
01:01:34,530 --> 01:01:37,130
The fact that I don't remember spending time with you...

786
01:01:40,000 --> 01:01:42,099
means I didn't do anything for you.

787
01:01:58,150 --> 01:01:59,719
It's all in the past.

788
01:02:02,190 --> 01:02:03,460
And I've forgotten it all.

789
01:02:04,860 --> 01:02:07,460
Have you really forgotten it all?

790
01:02:08,460 --> 01:02:10,000
When you get out of the hospital,

791
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:13,940
make me home-cooked food.

792
01:02:15,639 --> 01:02:16,900
Nothing too spicy.

793
01:02:21,239 --> 01:02:22,280
Okay.

794
01:02:25,510 --> 01:02:27,519
(Iroun Genetic Center)

795
01:02:35,260 --> 01:02:37,860
I'm back here again.

796
01:02:39,829 --> 01:02:41,130
On my way here,

797
01:02:41,659 --> 01:02:44,829
I thought a lot about whether or not I was overstepping my bounds.

798
01:02:47,269 --> 01:02:48,840
But I've changed a bit.

799
01:02:49,269 --> 01:02:50,300
Yeon Woo...

800
01:02:51,039 --> 01:02:53,110
will go to the US today on the 8pm flight.

801
01:02:55,639 --> 01:02:57,750
I see.

802
01:03:02,619 --> 01:03:05,488
From this accident, I thought...

803
01:03:05,489 --> 01:03:09,019
Yeon Woo might really love you.

804
01:03:10,019 --> 01:03:11,759
He knows better than anyone...

805
01:03:11,760 --> 01:03:13,159
that hands are everything to a surgeon.

806
01:03:13,929 --> 01:03:17,599
But he gave up his hand for you.

807
01:03:19,829 --> 01:03:21,369
That seems like a miracle.

808
01:03:23,869 --> 01:03:25,940
Gave up his hand?

809
01:03:29,039 --> 01:03:30,280
Didn't you know?

810
01:03:32,309 --> 01:03:33,780
Because of the burn,

811
01:03:34,380 --> 01:03:36,449
Yeon Woo might not be able to hold a scalpel ever again.

812
01:03:37,889 --> 01:03:38,889
What?

813
01:03:40,389 --> 01:03:42,718
He definitely said it was okay...

814
01:03:42,719 --> 01:03:44,929
I'm sure he didn't want to tell you.

815
01:03:47,960 --> 01:03:49,960
You said it was the 8pm flight, right?

816
01:03:55,170 --> 01:03:58,369
Attention, please. Announcement for the flight...

817
01:04:02,280 --> 01:04:04,849
Why? Are you waiting for someone?

818
01:04:05,309 --> 01:04:06,309
Oh, no.

819
01:04:10,119 --> 01:04:11,389
Doctor.

820
01:04:11,650 --> 01:04:12,848
Hello.

821
01:04:12,849 --> 01:04:14,059
Ms. Yoo.

822
01:04:16,889 --> 01:04:17,889
